     "status" -> "None", "summary" -> 
    "BravyiGreen[ws, {k1, k2, ..., km}] returns m*m matrix G i j := \
\\[LeftAngleBracket]c Subscript[k, i] c_kj^\\[Dagger]\\ \\[RightAngleBracket] \
of Green's functions between fermion modes ki and kj with respect to Bravyi \
state ws. BravyiGreen[ns, {k1, k2, ..., km}] returns NambuGreen[{G, F}] with \
m*m matrices G i j := \\[LeftAngleBracket]c Subscript[k, i] c_kj^\\[Dagger]\\ \
\\[RightAngleBracket] and F i j := \\[LeftAngleBracket]c Subscript[k, i] c \
Subscript[k, j]\\[RightAngleBracket] of normal and anomalous Green's \
functions, respectively, between fermion modes ki and kj with respect to \
Bravyi state ns. BravyiGreen[in] is equivalent to BravyiGreen[in, Range[n]], \
where n is the number of fermion modes for which input Bravyi state in is \
defined for. BravyiGreen[data] or BravyiGreen[data, {k1, k2, ...}] shows a \
dynamic progress indicator while calculating Green's functions for an \
(typically large) array data of Bravyi states. ", "synonyms" -> {}, 
    "tabletags" -> {}, "title" -> "BravyiGreen", "titlemodifier" -> "", 
    "metadescription" -> "", "windowtitle" -> "BravyiGreen", "type" -> 
    "Symbol", "uri" -> "QuantumMob/Q3/ref/BravyiGreen"}},
